# Protected Files — DO NOT modify without explicit user approval

These files are stable and critical. Changing them risks breaking the system.
If a task requires modifying a protected file, STOP and ask the user first.

## Never Modify (existing migrations)
- `migrations/001-NNN` — existing business migrations. Create NEW migrations instead.
- `src/core/db/migrations/001-NNN` — core infrastructure migrations. Always add new.

## Ask Before Modifying (stable infrastructure)
- `src/core/auth/` — JWT, RBAC, sessions
- `src/core/db/connection.js` — database foundation
- `src/core/security/` — input sanitizer, CSRF, prompt guard
- `src/bridge/openclaw-client.js` — WebSocket handshake, reconnection
- `server.js` / `src/boot.js` — startup sequence
- `.claude/settings.json` — hooks and permissions
- `package.json` dependencies — no add/remove without reason

## Why These Are Protected
Each has downstream dependencies across the codebase:
- auth middleware → all API endpoints
- db connection → all modules and migrations
- boot sequence → initialization order matters
- bridge client → all agent communication
